&ldquo;I&rsquo;m not done talking to you, Hyung.&rdquo;
What is this asshole jabbering about now?
&ldquo;I don't care how much money your family has -- to freakin&rsquo; look down on and treat a person like a beggar, how do you think that would make me feel?&rdquo;
Jeong-in was confused as to whether the person in front of him was the same Jo Seung Hyun he had known up till now.
&ldquo;Seung-hyun, I think you&rsquo;re misunderstanding something, I was just innocently&hellip;&rdquo;  
&ldquo;You sure like acting innocent.&rdquo; 
Seung-hyun again pinched his lips. It was only then that Jeong-in realized he was holding back laughter. 
&ldquo;....Jo Seung Hyun.&rdquo;
You and Han Min-woo have even slept together like dogs, that kind of word doesn't suit you. 
&ldquo;&hellip;&hellip;W-what?&rdquo;

&ldquo;Didn&rsquo;t you hear me? You and Han Min-woo have even fucked like dogs, so I asked how do you have the audacity to say the word innocent? 
He had no choice but to doubt his ears. Jeong-in got goosebumps without realizing it and pulled his head back.
&ldquo;Hyung, you don&rsquo;t even have the basics down.&rdquo;
There was a wrinkle between Jeong-in's fair eyes. His breath became rough because he could not control his anger. Seeing him in such a state, Seung-hyun grinned. 
&quot;&hellip;&hellip;to make a deal, you should have asked me what I wanted first.&quot;
&ldquo;&hellip;&hellip;.&rdquo;
&quot;What a fool.&quot;
 Bam. Someone seemed to hit his head hard.
